---
export const prerender = false;
---
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8" />
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
<meta name="robots" content="noindex, nofollow" />
<title>Orient — Pricing (internal draft)</title>
<meta name="description" content="Internal pricing draft for Orient — how the meaning system is packaged from a single team to the whole organisation." />
<link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com" />
<link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin />
<link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Spectral:ital,wght@0,300;0,400;0,500;0,600;1,400;1,500&family=IBM+Plex+Sans:wght@400;500;600&family=IBM+Plex+Mono:wght@400;500&display=swap" rel="stylesheet" />
<link rel="stylesheet" href="/orient.css" />
<link rel="stylesheet" href="/landing.css" />
<link rel="stylesheet" href="/pricing.css?v=1" />
</head>
<body class="pr-page">

<!-- ============ INTERNAL BANNER ============ -->
<div class="pr-banner">
  <div class="wrap">
    <span class="dot"></span>
    <p><b>Internal draft</b> — not linked in navigation. All figures are placeholders for review and will be password-protected before sharing.</p>
    <p class="right"><a href="/strategy">Strategy →</a></p>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- ============ HEADER ============ -->
<header class="site-header" id="header">
  <div class="wrap bar">
    <a href="/" class="brand" aria-label="Orient — home">
      <img src="/logo.svg" alt="Orient" class="brand-logo" />
    </a>
    <nav class="site-nav">
      <a href="/">What is Orient</a>
      <a href="/forhumans">For Humans</a>
      <a href="/formachines">For Machines</a>
      <a href="/usecases">Use cases</a>
      <a href="/opinion">Opinion</a>
      <a href="/trust">Trust</a>
      <a href="/about">About</a>
    </nav>
    <button class="btn" data-scroll="#access">Request access</button>
  </div>
</header>

<main id="top">

  <!-- ============ HERO ============ -->
  <section class="pr-hero">
    <div class="wrap">
      <span class="eyebrow">Pricing</span>
      <h1>Pricing that scales with shared meaning.</h1>
      <p class="lede">Start with a single team and grow to the whole organisation. <b>Orient for Humans</b> is priced per seat; <b>Orient for Machines</b> — the meaning layer your agents act on — is metered by usage. Pick a tier below, or combine both.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ============ TIERS ============ -->
  <section class="section" style="padding-top:8px">
    <div class="wrap">
      <div class="pr-tiers">

        <!-- Team -->
        <div class="pr-tier">
          <div class="scale">Team</div>
          <p class="for">For a single team thinking and communicating together.</p>
          <div class="pr-price"><span class="amt">$36</span><span class="per">/ seat / month</span></div>
          <p class="pr-sub">billed annually · or $43 monthly · from 3 seats</p>
          <a class="cta" href="#access">Get started</a>
          <ul class="pr-inc">
            <li class="h">Includes</li>
            <li class="feat">Orient for Humans — full thinking &amp; communicating space</li>
            <li class="feat">Capture, Resolve, Frame, Measure &amp; Remember</li>
            <li class="feat">Unlimited seats in one team space</li>
            <li class="feat">Frames, exports &amp; shared library</li>
            <li class="feat">Community support</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <!-- Organisation -->
        <div class="pr-tier feature">
          <div class="scale">Organisation <span class="pill">Most teams</span></div>
          <p class="for">For many teams sharing one resolved understanding — and the agents acting on it.</p>
          <div class="pr-price"><span class="amt">$55</span><span class="per">/ seat / month</span></div>
          <p class="pr-sub">billed annually · or $66 monthly · includes meaning-layer base</p>
          <a class="cta" href="#access">Get started</a>
          <ul class="pr-inc">
            <li class="h">Everything in Team, plus</li>
            <li class="feat">Orient for Humans across every team</li>
            <li class="feat m">Orient for Machines — meaning layer for your agents</li>
            <li class="feat m">100k agent context calls / month included</li>
            <li class="feat">Impact analytics &amp; comprehension</li>
            <li class="feat">Advanced roles, audit logs &amp; priority support</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <!-- Enterprise -->
        <div class="pr-tier">
          <div class="scale">Enterprise</div>
          <p class="for">For organisations running on agents at scale, with security and controls.</p>
          <div class="pr-price custom"><span class="amt">Custom</span></div>
          <p class="pr-sub">annual contract · volume seats &amp; usage</p>
          <a class="cta" href="#access">Talk to us</a>
          <ul class="pr-inc">
            <li class="h">Everything in Organisation, plus</li>
            <li class="feat m">Full Machines API, grounding &amp; guardrails</li>
            <li class="feat">SSO / SAML, SCIM &amp; data residency</li>
            <li class="feat">Custom usage, agent policies &amp; constraints</li>
            <li class="feat">Dedicated onboarding &amp; success</li>
            <li class="feat">Custom SLA &amp; security review</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ============ TWO PRODUCT MODELS ============ -->
  <section class="section pr-models">
    <div class="wrap">
      <div class="section-head reveal">
        <span class="eyebrow">How each product is priced</span>
        <h2>Two products, two pricing models.</h2>
        <p>Humans pay for seats — people thinking and communicating. Machines pay for usage — the meaning agents read and act on. Most organisations run both.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="pr-models-grid">

        <div class="pr-model h">
          <div class="tag">Orient for Humans</div>
          <h3>Per seat</h3>
          <p class="model-line">subscription · monthly or annual</p>
          <p>A seat is one person with a named login who can capture, resolve, frame, measure and remember inside the team's space.</p>
          <ul class="pr-meter">
            <li><span class="k">Team</span><span class="v">$36 / seat / mo</span></li>
            <li><span class="k">Organisation</span><span class="v">$55 / seat / mo</span></li>
            <li><span class="k">Enterprise</span><span class="v">Volume / custom</span></li>
            <li><span class="k">Annual discount</span><span class="v">~2 months free</span></li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="pr-model m">
          <div class="tag">Orient for Machines</div>
          <h3>Per usage</h3>
          <p class="model-line">metered · agent context calls</p>
          <p>Agents read structured meaning — what is true, supported, contested, decided and safe to say — through the API. Priced by context calls beyond the included allowance.</p>
          <ul class="pr-meter">
            <li><span class="k">Included (Organisation)</span><span class="v">100k calls / mo</span></li>
            <li><span class="k">Additional usage</span><span class="v">$— / 1k calls</span></li>
            <li><span class="k">Grounding &amp; guardrails</span><span class="v">Standard / Advanced</span></li>
            <li><span class="k">Enterprise</span><span class="v">Committed-use rates</span></li>
          </ul>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ============ COMPARISON ============ -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="wrap">
      <div class="section-head reveal">
        <span class="eyebrow">Compare plans</span>
        <h2>What's included at each tier.</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="pr-compare-wrap">
        <table class="pr-compare">
          <thead>
            <tr>
              <th>Feature</th>
              <th>Team</th>
              <th class="feature-h">Organisation</th>
              <th>Enterprise</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr class="grp"><td colspan="4">Orient for Humans</td></tr>
            <tr><td class="k">Thinking &amp; communicating space</td><td><span class="yes">✓</span></td><td><span class="yes">✓</span></td><td><span class="yes">✓</span></td></tr>
            <tr><td class="k">Capture · Resolve · Frame · Measure · Remember</td><td><span class="yes">✓</span></td><td><span class="yes">✓</span></td><td><span class="yes">✓</span></td></tr>
            <tr><td class="k">Team spaces</td><td><span class="val">Single team</span></td><td><span class="val">Multiple teams</span></td><td><span class="val">Org-wide</span></td></tr>
            <tr><td class="k">Seats</td><td><span class="val">Unlimited</span></td><td><span class="val">Unlimited</span></td><td><span class="val">Unlimited</span></td></tr>
            <tr><td class="k">Frames, exports &amp; shared library</td><td><span class="yes">✓</span></td><td><span class="yes">✓</span></td><td><span class="yes">✓</span></td></tr>
            <tr><td class="k">Impact analytics &amp; comprehension</td><td><span class="no">—</span></td><td><span class="yes">✓</span></td><td><span class="yes">✓</span></td></tr>

            <tr class="grp"><td colspan="4">Orient for Machines</td></tr>
            <tr><td class="k">Meaning layer API</td><td><span class="no">—</span></td><td><span class="yes m">✓</span></td><td><span class="yes m">✓</span></td></tr>
            <tr><td class="k">Agent context calls / month</td><td><span class="no">—</span></td><td><span class="val">100k included</span></td><td><span class="val">Custom</span></td></tr>
            <tr><td class="k">Grounding &amp; guardrails</td><td><span class="no">—</span></td><td><span class="val">Standard</span></td><td><span class="val">Advanced</span></td></tr>
            <tr><td class="k">Agent policies &amp; constraints</td><td><span class="no">—</span></td><td><span class="yes m">✓</span></td><td><span class="yes m">✓</span></td></tr>

            <tr class="grp"><td colspan="4">Security &amp; admin</td></tr>
            <tr><td class="k">Roles &amp; permissions</td><td><span class="val">Basic</span></td><td><span class="val">Advanced</span></td><td><span class="val">Advanced</span></td></tr>
            <tr><td class="k">SSO / SAML · SCIM</td><td><span class="no">—</span></td><td><span class="val">Add-on</span></td><td><span class="yes">✓</span></td></tr>
            <tr><td class="k">Audit logs</td><td><span class="no">—</span></td><td><span class="yes">✓</span></td><td><span class="yes">✓</span></td></tr>
            <tr><td class="k">Data residency</td><td><span class="no">—</span></td><td><span class="no">—</span></td><td><span class="yes">✓</span></td></tr>

            <tr class="grp"><td colspan="4">Support</td></tr>
            <tr><td class="k">Support</td><td><span class="val">Community</span></td><td><span class="val">Priority</span></td><td><span class="val">Dedicated</span></td></tr>
            <tr><td class="k">Onboarding</td><td><span class="val">Self-serve</span></td><td><span class="val">Guided</span></td><td><span class="val">White-glove</span></td></tr>
            <tr><td class="k">SLA</td><td><span class="no">—</span></td><td><span class="val">99.9%</span></td><td><span class="val">Custom</span></td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>

      <div class="pr-note">
        <div class="card">
          <h4>How Machines usage is metered</h4>
          <p>Every time an agent reads structured meaning through the API, that's a context call. Organisation includes 100k / month; additional usage is billed per 1,000 calls, with committed-use rates at Enterprise.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h4>Annual vs monthly</h4>
          <p>Annual billing is the default and includes roughly two months free versus paying month to month. Seats can be added at any time and are prorated.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ============ FAQ ============ -->
  <section class="section pr-faq">
    <div class="wrap">
      <div class="section-head reveal">
        <span class="eyebrow">Questions</span>
        <h2>Pricing FAQ.</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="pr-faq-grid">
        <div class="pr-q">
          <h4>Do I need both products?</h4>
          <p>No. Many teams start with <b>Orient for Humans</b> alone. <b>Orient for Machines</b> becomes available from the Organisation tier, when you want agents acting on the same meaning.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="pr-q">
          <h4>What counts as a seat?</h4>
          <p>One named person who can work inside Orient. Read-only or guest access does not consume a seat.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="pr-q">
          <h4>How is the meaning layer priced?</h4>
          <p>By agent context calls. Organisation includes a monthly allowance; beyond that you pay per 1,000 calls. Enterprise uses committed-use pricing.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="pr-q">
          <h4>Can we move between tiers?</h4>
          <p>Yes. Upgrade at any time; changes are prorated. The Organisation tier is designed as the natural step once meaning is shared across teams.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="pr-q">
          <h4>Is there a minimum?</h4>
          <p>Team starts at 3 seats. Organisation and Enterprise are sized to your rollout — talk to us for a plan.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="pr-q">
          <h4>What about security &amp; data residency?</h4>
          <p>SSO/SAML, SCIM, audit logs and data residency are available at Enterprise, with a full security review on request.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ============ CLOSING CTA ============ -->
  <section class="closing" id="access">
    <div class="wrap">
      <img src="/logomark.svg" alt="" class="closing-mark" />
      <h2>Find the right plan.</h2>
      <p>Tell us about your team and how your agents will use Orient, and we'll shape a plan with you.</p>
      <form class="waitlist onink" data-waitlist data-redirect="/request-access" data-success="On the list ✓" style="justify-content:center">
        <input type="email" name="email" placeholder="you@company.com" aria-label="Work email" required />
        <button class="btn" type="submit">Request access</button>
      </form>
    </div>
  </section>
</main>

<!-- ============ FOOTER ============ -->
<footer class="site-footer">
  <div class="wrap row">
    <a href="/" class="brand" aria-label="Orient — home">
      <img src="/logo-light.svg" alt="Orient" class="brand-logo footer-logo" />
    </a>
    <div class="line">A meaning operating system for humans and machines.</div>
    <div class="links">
      <a href="/">What is Orient</a>
      <a href="/forhumans">For Humans</a>
      <a href="/formachines">For Machines</a>
      <a href="/usecases">Use cases</a>
      <a href="/opinion">Opinion</a>
      <a href="/trust">Trust</a>
      <a href="/about">About</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</footer>

<script is:inline src="/landing.js"></script>
</body>
</html>
